article.headline: W. Illinois 57, IUPUI 55
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. -- Freshman Remy Roberts-Burnett drilled a 3-pointer with 0.5 seconds left to send Western Illinois to a 57-55 win over IUPUI on Saturday night. Roberts-Burnett had 11 points off the bench for Western Illinois (12-8, 6-5 Summit). Alex Young led all scorers with 22 points for IUPUI (8-15, 2-9). Ceola Clark led Western Illinois with 22 points, nine rebounds and eight assists. Young hit a 15-foot jumper with about two minutes to go to give IUPUI a 55-54 lead. Terell Parks scored 14 for Western Illinois, and Obi Emegano added 10. Christian Siakam scored 16 points and grabbed eight rebounds for IUPUI.
